, E.K. Piascik &amp; 
<collectorName id="187E348DED33FFB1FBFCF823FB40F807" box="[1135,1218,1941,1967]" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">A. Ang</collectorName>
, WPM#12-035
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED33FFB1FF54F80EFC8EF85E" pageId="33" pageNumber="184" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B534515BED33FFB1FF54F80EFC8EF85E" blockId="33.[151,1436,1796,2039]" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED33FFB1FF54F80EFECCF87A" bold="true" box="[199,334,1976,2002]" pageId="33" pageNumber="184">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is honor of Dr. Fred R. Wanless (1940–2017), the British arachnologist who made great contributions on the taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED33FFB1FD05F86AFC8AF85E" authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1841" box="[662,776,2012,2038]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="33" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Salticidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
