<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED31FFB3FF54F8A6FE39F83E" pageId="35" pageNumber="186" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B534515BED31FFB3FF54F8A6FE39F83E" blockId="35.[151,1437,1808,2015]" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED31FFB3FF54F8A6FEC0F882" bold="true" box="[199,322,1808,1834]" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED31FFB3FD17F8A7FCA4F882" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[644,806,1809,1835]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="35" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minotaurus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED31FFB3FD17F8A7FCA4F882" box="[644,806,1809,1835]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">C. minotaurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED31FFB3FCBDF8A6FC0BF882" bold="true" box="[814,905,1808,1834]" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED31FFB3FCBDF8A6FC0BF882" box="[814,905,1808,1834]" pageId="35" pageNumber="186" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the similar shape of median septum and the bulging spermathecae, but can be distinguished from the latter by the presence of CPSB on the cephalon (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED31FFB3FABDF882FA0DF8E6" box="[1326,1423,1844,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 176–182" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,185,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[151,1436,181,1642]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 176–182. Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (176, 179, 181) and female (177–178, 180, 182). 176–178. Habitus, in dorsal (176–177) and lateral (178) view; 179–180. Front view of carapace; 181, 182. Details of chelicera, dorsal (181) and back (182) view, arrows pointing to fang-like projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500841/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">Fig. 177</figureCitation>
), the short embolus coiled half a circle (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED31FFB3FDDAF8EEFD2CF8DA" box="[585,686,1880,1906]" captionStart="FIGURES 183–185" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1601,1625]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,417,1578]" captionTargetId="figure-135@36.[151,1437,417,1578]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 183–185. Palp of Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (183), ventral (184) and retrolateral (185) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500844" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500844/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">Figs 184</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED31FFB3FD28F8EEFD6AF8DA" box="[699,744,1880,1906]" captionStart="FIGURES 186–188" captionStartId="37.[151,264,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1296]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[151,1436,181,1297]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 186–188. Palp of Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (186), ventral (187) and retrolateral (188) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500846/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">187</figureCitation>
), the less coiled copulatory ducts, and the sub-spherical spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED31FFB3FE83F8CAFE2CF83E" box="[272,430,1916,1942]" captionStart="FIGURES 189–194" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1441,1465]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-19@38.[151,1436,181,1418]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 189–194. Female genitalia of Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 189, 190, 192. Ventral view; 191, 193. Dorsal view; 194. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500848/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">Figs 191, 193</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED31FFB5FF54F816FAAFF92E" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="188" pageId="35" pageNumber="186" type="description">
<paragraph id="B534515BED31FFB4FF54F816FB5BFE21" blockId="35.[151,1437,1808,2015]" lastBlockId="36.[151,1437,150,393]" lastPageId="36" lastPageNumber="187" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED31FFB3FF54F816FE26F812" bold="true" box="[199,420,1952,1978]" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED31FFB3FD06F816FD74F812" box="[661,758,1952,1978]" captionStart="FIGURES 176–182" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,185,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[151,1436,181,1642]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 176–182. Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (176, 179, 181) and female (177–178, 180, 182). 176–178. Habitus, in dorsal (176–177) and lateral (178) view; 179–180. Front view of carapace; 181, 182. Details of chelicera, dorsal (181) and back (182) view, arrows pointing to fang-like projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500841/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="186">Fig. 176</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 1.42; abdomen length 1.10. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.32, ALE 0.20, PME 0.07, PLE 0.18. Measurements of legs: I 2.36 (0.74, 0.38, 0.59, 0.36, 0.29), II 2.01 (0.63, 0.32, 0.43, 0.33, 0.30), III 1.93 (0.60, 0.20, 0.36, 0.44, 0.33), IV 1.97 (0.54, 0.22, 0.39, 0.50, 0.32). Chelicerae with fang-like projection distally (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED36FFB4FD0EFF0DFC82FF7D" box="[669,768,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 176–182" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,185,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[151,1436,181,1642]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 176–182. Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (176, 179, 181) and female (177–178, 180, 182). 176–178. Habitus, in dorsal (176–177) and lateral (178) view; 179–180. Front view of carapace; 181, 182. Details of chelicera, dorsal (181) and back (182) view, arrows pointing to fang-like projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500841/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Fig. 181</figureCitation>
); promargin with two teeth, retromargin with one bicuspid tooth. Palp (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED36FFB4FEB0FF69FE47FF51" box="[291,453,223,249]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 183–185" captionStart-1="FIGURES 186–188" captionStartId-0="36.[151,264,1601,1625]" captionStartId-1="37.[151,264,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1437,417,1578]" captionTargetBox-1="[152,1435,182,1296]" captionTargetId-0="figure-135@36.[151,1437,417,1578]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@37.[151,1436,181,1297]" captionTargetPageId-0="36" captionTargetPageId-1="37" captionText-0="FIGURES 183–185. Palp of Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (183), ventral (184) and retrolateral (185) view." captionText-1="FIGURES 186–188. Palp of Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (186), ventral (187) and retrolateral (188) view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500844" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500846" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6500844/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6500846/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Figs 183–188</figureCitation>
): embolus short, coiled half a circle; embolic disc small and sclerotized; LED narrow, not serrulate-edged; tegulum slightly sclerotized, tegular lobe present; retrolateral tibial apophysis wide at base and pointed apically in retrolateral view, tip slightly inner-curved in ventral view. Sternum without setal tuft. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED36FFB4FF6AFEFDFEDEFECE" box="[249,348,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURES 176–182" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,185,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[151,1436,181,1642]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 176–182. Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (176, 179, 181) and female (177–178, 180, 182). 176–178. Habitus, in dorsal (176–177) and lateral (178) view; 179–180. Front view of carapace; 181, 182. Details of chelicera, dorsal (181) and back (182) view, arrows pointing to fang-like projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500841/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Fig. 176</figureCitation>
): carapace reddish brown, with CPSB; dorsal abdomen pale yellow, with dark crux-shaped markings, not obviously sclerotized; ventral abdomen grayish brown; legs I–II darker than legs III–IV.
</paragraph>
<caption id="E1F401D3ED36FFB4FF04F9F7FED3F9D6" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500844" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6500844" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500844/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" startId="36.[151,264,1601,1625]" targetBox="[151,1437,417,1578]" targetPageId="36">
<paragraph id="B534515BED36FFB4FF04F9F7FED3F9D6" blockId="36.[151,1436,1601,1662]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED36FFB4FF04F9F7FEECF9F1" bold="true" box="[151,366,1601,1625]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">FIGURES 183–185.</emphasis>
Palp of 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED36FFB4FE51F9F4FC00F9F2" authority="Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[450,898,1602,1626]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wanlessi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED36FFB4FE51F9F4FD09F9F2" box="[450,651,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">Charippus wanlessi</emphasis>
Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED36FFB4FC1FF9F4FC5FF9F2" bold="true" box="[908,989,1602,1626]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED36FFB4FC1FF9F4FC5FF9F2" box="[908,989,1602,1626]" pageId="36" pageNumber="187" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, in prolateral (183), ventral (184) and retrolateral (185) view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="E1F401D3ED37FFB5FF04FA9CFED3FACE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500846" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6500846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500846/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="188" startId="37.[151,264,1322,1346]" targetBox="[152,1435,182,1296]" targetPageId="37">
<paragraph id="B534515BED37FFB5FF04FA9CFED3FACE" blockId="37.[151,1436,1322,1382]" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED37FFB5FF04FA9CFEECFAEA" bold="true" box="[151,366,1322,1346]" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">FIGURES 186–188.</emphasis>
Palp of 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED37FFB5FE51FA9CFC00FAEA" authority="Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[450,898,1322,1346]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="37" pageNumber="188" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wanlessi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED37FFB5FE51FA9CFD09FAEA" box="[450,651,1322,1346]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">Charippus wanlessi</emphasis>
Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED37FFB5FC1FFA9CFC5FFAEA" bold="true" box="[908,989,1322,1346]" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED37FFB5FC1FFA9CFC5FFAEA" box="[908,989,1322,1346]" pageId="37" pageNumber="188" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, in prolateral (186), ventral (187) and retrolateral (188) view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="B534515BED37FFB5FF54FA22FAAFF92E" blockId="37.[151,1437,1428,1707]" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED37FFB5FF54FA22FEA7FA06" bold="true" box="[199,293,1428,1454]" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">Female.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED37FFB5FDB7FA22FD46FA06" box="[548,708,1428,1454]" captionStart="FIGURES 176–182" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,185,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[151,1436,181,1642]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 176–182. Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (176, 179, 181) and female (177–178, 180, 182). 176–178. Habitus, in dorsal (176–177) and lateral (178) view; 179–180. Front view of carapace; 181, 182. Details of chelicera, dorsal (181) and back (182) view, arrows pointing to fang-like projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500841/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">Figs 177–178</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 1.57; abdomen length 1.22. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.31, ALE 0.20, PME 0.04, PLE 0.18. Measurements of legs: I 1.97 (0.83, 0.49, 0.60, 0.41, 0.24), II 2.13 (0.68, 0.36, 0.45, 0.36, 0.28), III 2.25 (0.76, 0.36, 0.42, 0.42, 0.29), IV 2.36 (0.73, 0.29, 0.52, 0.48, 0.34). Chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED37FFB5FF62F9B6FED2F9B2" box="[241,336,1536,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 176–182" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,185,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[151,1436,181,1642]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 176–182. Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (176, 179, 181) and female (177–178, 180, 182). 176–178. Habitus, in dorsal (176–177) and lateral (178) view; 179–180. Front view of carapace; 181, 182. Details of chelicera, dorsal (181) and back (182) view, arrows pointing to fang-like projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500841/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">Fig. 182</figureCitation>
) as in male but without fang-like projection. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED37FFB5FB9EF9B6FB2FF9B2" box="[1037,1197,1536,1562]" captionStart="FIGURES 176–182" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,185,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[151,1436,181,1642]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 176–182. Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (176, 179, 181) and female (177–178, 180, 182). 176–178. Habitus, in dorsal (176–177) and lateral (178) view; 179–180. Front view of carapace; 181, 182. Details of chelicera, dorsal (181) and back (182) view, arrows pointing to fang-like projections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500841/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">Figs 177–178</figureCitation>
): carapace and dorsal abdomen as in male, ventral abdomen pale yellow. Sternum as in male. Epigynum (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED37FFB5FBC1F992FAAFF996" box="[1106,1325,1572,1598]" captionStart="FIGURES 189–194" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1441,1465]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-19@38.[151,1436,181,1418]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 189–194. Female genitalia of Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 189, 190, 192. Ventral view; 191, 193. Dorsal view; 194. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500848/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">Figs 189–190, 192</figureCitation>
): window relatively small, rims weakly present, median septum wide; lateral depressions shallow and not obvious. Vulva (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED37FFB5FAF9F9FEFF7FF92E" captionStart="FIGURES 189–194" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1441,1465]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-19@38.[151,1436,181,1418]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 189–194. Female genitalia of Charippus wanlessi Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 189, 190, 192. Ventral view; 191, 193. Dorsal view; 194. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500848/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="188">Figs 191, 193</figureCitation>
): CD relatively short, swerving for three times; AG large and mitriform; spermathecae bulbous.
</paragraph>
